Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with identifying and tracking extremist users in social networks.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper presents a new set of operational capabilities to deal with the threat posed by online extremists in social networks.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper deals with the security threat posed by online extremists in social networks.
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possible category as the paper deals with the societal impact of online extremism.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a possible category as the paper deals with the behavior of online extremists in social networks.
